# 🚀 CareerFlow

### Job Application Tracker

CareerFlow is a full-stack web application built to help job seekers efficiently track and manage their job applications in one place. This project was created as a practical way to improve my skills in the MERN stack while solving a real-world problem during my job search.

---

## 📸 Preview

![Dashboard](./screenshot/dashboard.jpg)

---

## 📸 Features

- 📋 Add job applications (company, position, status, date, notes, location)
- ✏️ Edit job entries
- ❌ Delete applications
- 🔄 Instant UI updates (no page refresh)
- 🎯 Status-based color indicators

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

**Frontend**

- React + TypeScript
- ChakraUI

**Backend**

- Node.js
- Express.js

**Database**

- MongoDB (Mongoose)

---

## 📂 Folder Structure

careerflow/
├── client/ # React frontend
├── server/ # Express backend

---

## ⚙️ Installation

### Clone the repo

git clone https://github.com/your-username/career-flow.git
cd careerflow

### Install dependencies

cd client && npm install
cd ../server && npm install

### Setup environment variables

Create .env in /server:

MONGO_URI=your_mongodb_connection_string
PORT=5000

---

## ▶️ Run the App

**Backend**
cd server
npm run dev

**Frontend**
cd client
npm run dev

